Text: This past week the group met with OceanBrowser founders Rodney and Gloria for the first time to discuss the studio project.
The meeting went well, but it was clear Rodney had quite a different set of goals for the project than what the group had assumed from reading the brief.

This was initially a bit disorientating, but throughout the meeting we were able to narrow down their top priority - a command line interface query program that helps them easily query aggregate users statistics.

Upon reflection i would have done differently to make the meeting more productive would have been to try maintain the frame of discussion on addressing the questions and topics relating to our specific project goals.
This will be something i'll keep in mind for future meetings.
Following this initial meeting, we the group met a couple of times throughout the week and outlined how we will approach the development of the CLI.
We created some timeline milestones and began delegation for the project, all of which was reflected in our group presentation and project proposal.
We had another meeting with Rodney on Thursday to make sure we are on the same page and asked some more specific questions.
We also showed him some of our presentation, including Roro's CLI prototype which he seemed very happy about.
He mentioned that he is talking to his lead developer about creating a mock database that we can use to test the product, and was able to supply us with this on Saturday.

My thoughts now are that some of the learning goals are probably not going to be necessary for the project, but i do see the interesting aspects of creating a working CLI with javascript could be equally as interesting.
I have been looking into commander.
js an trying to get a grasp on how that works.
In summary, I think we have achieved this weeks goal of understanding what Rodney and Gloria want to get out of the project.
Our goals for this coming week are to get more familiar with the technology and advance the prototype closer toward a finished product, and to organise a focus group.
This will include reading more documentation on Cassandra databases, setting up a VM on Ubuntu, looking more into R, and understanding the node, Inquirer and commander aspects.
